            <bug_when>2009-12-15 02:20:26 +0000</bug_when>
            <thetext>Currently, if you want to index multiple branches in a git repository, you have to have separate clones with the appropriate branch checked out in each one. While this works, it&apos;s clumsy, especially for repositories with lots of branches. It would be much better if OpenGrok could index all the branches in a single clone, perhaps even a bare clone (one with no working copy). This should be possible, but it would require using some of git&apos;s plumbing commands, or perhaps JGit (the pure-Java implementation of git).</thetext>
          </long_desc>
      
      

